manifest.name: Marketplace Extension
manifest.author: Llydia Cross
manifest.description: Enables marketplace functionality inside of InfinityMint.

manifest.name: ERC721 Redemption Tools
manifest.author: Llydia Cross
manifest.description: Offers two forms of redemption for ERC721 tokens. The first method is a passcode based system which doesn't need any wallets to be set up. The second is classic Merkle Tree requiring addresses.

approveRedeem(uint256,bytes).notice: Approves a request to redeem a token

onERC721Received(address,address,uint256.notice: Allows this redemption contract to receive ERC721 from approved addresses only

rejectRedeem(uint256).notice: Rejects a request to redeem a token

requestToken(uint256,bytes,bytes).notice: Requests a token to be transfered to the sender

approve(address,uint256).details: will Throw if tokenId does not exist

ownerOf(uint256).details: will Throw if the token does not exist

approve(address,uint256).notice: Sets an approved adress for this token

balanceOf(address).notice: blanceOf returns the number of tokens an address currently holds.

exists(uint256).notice: Returns true if a token exists.

getApproved(uint256).notice: Returns the approved adress for this token.

isApprovedForAll(address,address).notice: Will returns true if the operator is approved by the owner address

isApprovedOrOwner(address,uint256).notice: will returns true if the address is apprroved for all, approved operator or is the owner of a token

name().notice: Returns the name of the ERC721  for display on places like Etherscan

ownerOf(uint256).notice: Returns the owner of a current token

Just like transferFrom except we will check if the to address is a contract and is an IERC721Receiver implementer

setApprovalForAll(address,bool).notice: Will approve an operator for the senders tokens

tokenURI(uint256).notice: Returns the tokens URI Metadata object

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).notice: Transfers a token fsrom one address to another. Use safeTransferFrom as that will double check that the address you send this token too is a contract that can actually receive it.

wallet.title: Wallet Expansion (ERC721 Receiver)
wallet.description: Allows the token to act like a wallet, it will be able to hold ERC721 tokens as well as ERC20 tokens. Required for many links to work.

stickers.title: EADS Sticker Controller
stickers.description: Allows your token access to the Ethereum Ad Network, a sponsorship model which enables stickers to be placed onto your token for a price that you set.

proof_of_redemption.title: 🗺️ Proof Of Redemption
proof_of_redemption.description: Did you redeem your token through our neat redemption system? Then we have a surprise for you! Lets link that to your tokenId so that future owners will know this happened and you shall get a free NFT.

multiminter.title: MultiMinter Receiver
multiminter.description: Allows the token receive special MultiMinter tokens. Required for many links to work.
